This epistle is addressed to Maecenas, who, it would seem, had been urging our poet to resume his lyre, and to produce more odes. The substanceof his reply is, that he had become too old to indulge any longer in these trlfles ς that the study of philoso- phy, of truth, and of duty, was more becoming his years, and bet- ter suited to his taste. He likewise intimates that he had already gained some reputation as a lyric poet, which it was not worth his while to risk by any further efforts in this way.
